sertions. If the assertions are enabled in the image, would calling `setClassAssertionStatus` at runtime be too late? But what if the native image class is indeed initialized at runtime? Most application classes are initialized during runtime, not at build time. There's a lot to consider here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Added a dedicated test for `com.sun.jna.platform.win32.COM.util.CallbackProxy`:\n\n- `tests/src/net.java.dev.jna/jna-platform/5.3.1/src/test/java/net_java_dev_jna/jna_platform/CallbackProxyTest.java`\n\nThe test:\n- Constructs `CallbackProxy` with an annotated COM event interface, covering `Class#getMethods()` in `createDispIdMap`.\n- Invokes the public dispatch path with a matching `DISPID`, covering `Method#invoke(...)` in `invokeOnThread`.\n- Keeps the test platform-neutral by disabling only `CallbackProxy`’s debug COM-initialization assertion before class initialization.\n\nI did not run tests, per the workflow instructions.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0b8a85f28743fd750169f97ec4a2e081a2ba55953cca522a16\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1541, "output": 756, "cacheRead": 43008, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 45305, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777958584103, "responseId": "resp_0b8a85f28743fd750169f97eb8acd481a29b1cdf2fdb734ba0"}}
